title: After Alex Pretti's death in Minneapolis, Trump's strategy of tension comes under scrutiny
subhed: The American president has tried to persuade public opinion that Democrats and protesters were to blame for the violence caused by his immigration policy. The largest city in Minnesota, where federal agents killed a second person on Saturday, has become his testing ground.
byline: By Nicolas Chapuis (New York (United States) correspondent)

title: 'Agreements between the EU and India are a way to show the world there are alternatives to the US'
subhed: The European Commission president is expected to sign a free trade agreement with India that has been negotiated for years, writes political scientist Christophe Jaffrelot, a specialist on India.

title: Russia steps up attacks on Ukraine's shipping routes in the Black Sea
subhed: Airstrikes on Ukrainian ports have intensified since December 2025. Without a fleet, Kyiv has nevertheless managed to secure grain and container traffic, but the threat of attacks by naval drones is drawing closer.

title: François Kollar shines a light on Parisian workers between the World Wars
subhed: A former lathe operator at Renault, François Kollar became one of the leading photographers of the industrial world in interwar France. Between 1931 and 1934, he traveled across the country to photograph workers on the job. Several photographs from this series, taken in Paris, have been selected by the Musée Carnavalet for an exhibition dedicated to the capital city's residents.

title: Gabriel Attal pushes ahead with presidential bid, despite doubts within party
subhed: Criticized internally for his political positioning and strategy, the former French prime minister rejects comparisons with his longtime mentor, Emmanuel Macron.

France is considering banning phones in high schools. This school near Paris already does.
subhed: The Lycée Michelet, a large school complex with 2,300 students, banned mobile phones in its hallways in April 2025. School officials report positive results from a decision made in agreement with the entire educational community.

title: US seeks to use Alberta to destabilize Canada
subhed: The Trump administration and MAGA circles are closely watching the conservative, oil-rich province, particularly as a separatist movement has launched a campaign to organize an independence referendum.

title: Generative AI, psychiatry and the risks of self-service therapy
subhed: Millions of people use chatbots like ChatGPT to share their distress, and the scientific community has warned about the risks vulnerable people face. Generative AI has shaken up psychiatric consultations, fueled tech giants' ambitions and emerged as a credible tool for analyzing pathologies.
